This paper discusses the conversion of a Shannon's channel into a semantic channel for machine learning, which involves topics such as information theory, artificial intelligence, natural language processing, and cryptography. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
